gomodel:SYNGO_5197  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4, S5: STED super-resolution microscopy of hippocampal neurons stained for SynDIG4 (PRRT1), TARP-γ8 (CACNG8) and Homer (HOMER1) showed localization of CACNG8 to postsynaptic densities.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Primary neuronal culture - Hippocampi were dissected from E18 wildtype mice ...\"\n\nantibody:\n\"Anti-TARP-γ8 (AB_2572272, rabbit, Frontier Institute, Ishikari-shi, Japan) was used for immunocytochemistry at 1:100.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
